To calculate the Gibbs free energy change (ΔG) for the reaction, we use the formula:

ΔG = Σ ΔG(products) - Σ ΔG(reactants)

ΔG = [2 * (-14.50370329271722) + (-10.545928640174065)] - [2 * (-18.632139372623293)]
